<subSubSection id="9EE8B64937AE4FB82E524844027E9921" pageId="4" pageNumber="127" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="2AC41F3A681E81701836767468D74D0D" pageId="4" pageNumber="127">
<taxonomicName id="D338FB07C0A801FF4B2068B018677902" class="Insecta" family="Zygaenidae" genus="Zygaena" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Zygaena rhadamanthus subsp. aurargentea" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="127" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="rhadamanthus" subSpecies="aurargentea">Zygaena rhadamanthus aurargentea</taxonomicName>
Mazel, 1979, Entomops, Nice 6: 267, figs 1, 2 (
<taxonomicName id="EAA9BAED9B8F668D3E6C550A0A9572EC" class="Insecta" family="Zygaenidae" genus="Zygaena" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Zygaena" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="127" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Zygaena</taxonomicName>
). Type-locality. France: 
<normalizedToken id="4A08D51C4E37262FD66F26B4FD7A7C96" originalValue="Pyrénées-Orientales">Pyrenees-Orientales</normalizedToken>
, Coustouges.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="3F32AFBD344B6B4791C57C91F353539D" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="128" pageId="4" pageNumber="127" type="distribution and taxonomic notes">
<paragraph id="D6C7BC3B44142C0C4CDFAC40AED90BFF" pageId="4" pageNumber="127">Distribution and taxonomic notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2CE002273A1E90B3781513E130E90970" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="128" pageId="4" pageNumber="127">
Described from Coustouges (
<normalizedToken id="865182812C0BBFBFA187B89FFD93B3BB" originalValue="Pyrénées-Orientales">Pyrenees-Orientales</normalizedToken>
, France), 
<taxonomicName id="4AC68B075BEF589E3944EE990715AD7E" class="Insecta" family="Zygaenidae" genus="Zygaena" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Zygaena rhadamanthus subsp. aurargentea" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="128" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="rhadamanthus" subSpecies="aurargentea">
<pageBreakToken id="6033CCBC36BBB6738B49FAC9C916D5D6" pageId="5" pageNumber="128" start="start">Zygaena</pageBreakToken>
rhadamanthus aurargentea
</taxonomicName>
is also found in Spain (Barcelona and Gerona, excluding coastal regions). It is distinguished from 
<taxonomicName id="A0B5A9A09937EE218DCCF9FA2C6E34E6" class="Insecta" family="Zygaenidae" genus="Zygaena" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Zygaena rhadamanthus subsp. rhadamanthus" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="128" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="rhadamanthus" subSpecies="rhadamanthus">Zygaena rhadamanthus rhadamanthus</taxonomicName>
by the extreme griseoid phenotype, i.e. with pronounced white scaling on the ground colour of the forewings, especially in the females, which is reminiscent of 
<taxonomicName id="BD688D754DF20904307EB231FB1C9212" class="Insecta" family="Zygaenidae" genus="Zygaena" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Zygaena rhadamanthus subsp. grisea" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="128" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="rhadamanthus" subSpecies="grisea">Zygaena rhadamanthus grisea</taxonomicName>
from south-eastern and southern-central France (see above), and by the presence of a strong abdominal cingulum that is also present ventrally. 
<bibRefCitation id="B9862698336748813F2F2D95F080284B" author="Leraut, P" journalOrPublisher="NAP Editions, Verrieres-le Buisson" pageId="7" pageNumber="130" title="Volume 3: Moths of Europe, Zygaenids, Pyralids 1 and Brachodids." year="2012">Leraut (2012</bibRefCitation>
: 98) placed 
<taxonomicName id="8365F2A0F7751947A733A5F5286CF9B4" class="Insecta" family="Zygaenidae" genus="Zygaena" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Zygaena rhadamanthus subsp. aurargentea" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="128" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="rhadamanthus" subSpecies="aurargentea">Zygaena rhadamanthus aurargentea</taxonomicName>
as a synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="4604CAD4B549923B2AA86C83DE4187F4" class="Insecta" family="Zygaenidae" genus="Zygaena" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Zygaena rhadamanthus subsp. cleui" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="128" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="rhadamanthus" subSpecies="cleui">Zygaena rhadamanthus cleui</taxonomicName>
, which he reinstated as a valid subspecies, but we see no justification for this (see also above). The former is here reinstated (stat. rev.) as a valid subspecies, based on its extreme phenotype, which is so strongly different from that of the nominotypical taxon 
<taxonomicName id="559099BC1F823E9953760D13D9AF2BF0" class="Insecta" family="Zygaenidae" genus="Zygaena" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Zygaena rhadamanthus subsp. rhadamanthus" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="128" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="rhadamanthus" subSpecies="rhadamanthus">Zygaena rhadamanthus rhadamanthus</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="84C167EFBDF728256EE4512F4C5A96D6" author="Hofmann, A" journalOrPublisher="Harley Books, Colchester" pageId="7" pageNumber="130" title="A systematic Catalogue of the Zygaeninae (Lepidoptera: Zygaenidae)." year="1996">Hofmann and Tremewan 1996</bibRefCitation>
: 131).
</paragraph>
